history.content: The EECS 101 Piazza is a primarily an undergraduate page (sorry that's not more clear). We're not able to advise on graduate matters or courses. Please contact your new Adviser, Michael Sun <msun86@eecs.berkeley.edu>

children.subject: If you emailed Michael Sun, do you mind telling me what he said? I am having the exact same problem.

history.content:
Here's the response I got from him: 

"I've received a couple of inquiries about being waitlisted to CS 294-112 and all I can say at the moment is that it's probably intentional. I will contact the CS scheduler to see why the restrictions are set but she is currently swamped with undergraduate and transfer student enrollment issues. I'm fairly sure you will be able to get into the course."

I'm entering the 5th Year Masters program in the fall, and CS 294-112 has seats reserved for EECS grad students, and only 40/75 of them have been filled (according to the schedule planner).  However, I'm unable to enroll in the class, and am on the waitlist.  Is this intended, or is this a bug that will be resolved soon? 

Also, if I recall correctly, this class used to be a 4 unit class.  I was hoping this semester would be similar because I won't have to take 4 EECS courses to reach the 10 unit requirement for the Masters and can focus on research instead.  Is there any plan for this (or any of the grad classes) to be raised to a 4 unit class?
